cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a novel descriptor for image matching using a Siamese architecture and machine learning techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks to learn the feature embedding, which suggests it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also evaluates its proposed method on a challenging dataset, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of floating-point descriptors and optimization techniques suggests it could also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
